      <h2 class="text-center">Best Inspiring Books Written By Dr APJ Abdul Kalam</h2>
      <div class="col-sm-6"></div>
      <p>Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam, the 11th President of India, will always inspire every citizen of the country. Born in the small town of Rameshwaram, Tamil Nadu, he achieved the position of the President of India through his hard work, perseverance, and dedication. He had handled a key role both in Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) and the Defence Research and Development Organisation (DRDO). Popularly known as the Missile Man of India, Abdul Kalam passed away on 27th July 2015, yet ..
      </p>
      <div class="card" style="width: 18rem;">
        <img src="./asset/image/wings-of-fire-an-autobiography kalam1.webp" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="Wings of Fire:">Wings of Fire:</h5>
          <p class="card-text">This is Dr. Kalam's autobiography, which he co-wrote with Arun Tiwari, an Indian missile scientist, professor, and published author. It narrates Dr. Kalam's early childhood and the set of circumstances that led to his career decision, his work at NASA and other institutions for all those years, and his genesis story as the Missile Man of India.
            </p>
